title: personal browsing history
extract: Incognito Mode, Chrome's version of private browsing, can be accessed from the settings menu at the top right of the browser, or by pushing Ctrl+Shift+N. ... Google Chrome won't save your browsing history, store cookies and site data, or any personal information you use to fill out forms.Nov 20, 2018
